    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.10-11_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">10</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">TWEEDSMUIR,
                        <lb/>
                        KANAWHA FALLS,
                            <lb/>
                            WEST VIRGINIA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>11 July 1958</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Doctor Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>When the mail came yesterday, I wept. Since coming to America, I have been reading your poems and loving them. Among the short poems, the ones I like best are: Let Me Live Out My Years in Heat of Blood; Easter; If This Be Sin; and Let Down Your Hair.</p>
                
                <p>Others have kissed you with their lips. I kiss you with my heart. I shall keep this poem always.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Believe me, my honored friend,</salute>
                
                    <salute>Most faithfully yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Birgit Svendsen <!-- name from j4a.26a.113-114 --></signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Branson</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
